OL,3,CMan allegedly murdered by his wife had
OL,4,C'threatened to shoot neighbours' dog'
OL,6,FRebecca Squire said she was "always
OL,7,Fnervous" of Ian Rawle, and described
OL,8,Fseveral incidents in which he would
OL,9,Fcomplain about building renovations or
OL,10,Foutdoor lighting.
OL,12,F"He once cut the wire to our security
OL,13,Flight," she said.
OL,15,F"He banged on our door at 3am to say
OL,16,Fit wasn't 'effing Blackpool
OL,17,Filluminations'."
OL,19,FMrs Squire recalled another occasion
OL,20,Fwhere she was in her car and suspected
OL,21,FMr Rawle was following her.
